data.text:
Second only to that damn Mariah song (you know the one) “Last Christmas” is one of the most mashed-up holiday songs ever. Originally released in 1984 by the U.K. pop duo Wham!, it has since become such a nearly-unavoidable seasonal standard that there’s even a challenge called “Whamaggedon” where one attempts to make it through the month of December without hearing the song once.

Fortunately, mashups, remixes, and covers are disqualified from the rules of Whamaggedon, so this album is safe for listening – IF YOU DARE! Not sure who would want to listen to 42 different mashups of the SAME DAMN SONG, but if you’re looking to troll a holiday party with a playlist of a (mostly) beloved Christmas classic, this is for you!

Hit the Mashup Player in the lower left to stream the entire playlist (or download the zip file of all the MP3s). Or just pick and choose your favorites. Merry Christmash!

This year’s Best of Bootie Mashup mixtape is a little different than previous years, in that it’s almost a three-part suite. The first section jumps right in with dance-pop disco vibes, kicking things off with a mashup of Dua Lipa’s “Dance The Night,” the showcase single from the year’s biggest movie, “Barbie.” (Not so coincidentally, “Barbie” also was the theme of our biggest party in 2023.)

We always have an EDM mashup section on the album, but this year we get to the bangers sooner, and stay there longer, to keep you pumped on the dancefloor. Then it’s time for the third and final stretch, with a long tail of inventive, mostly genre-clashed mashups, including a block of Taylor Swift tracks (after all, this was certainly her year) and the requisite chill-out (and WTF) mashups to take us to the end.

We always try to include as many “big hits” of the year as we can, as well as showcasing throwback tracks that got a makeover by being mashed up in creative ways. Special shout-out to DJ Firth for mixing this year’s edition, and Adriana A for curating the Bootie Mashup team’s favorites.

And for the first time since 2005, there are NO Bonus Tracks! All killer, no filler!

Four years ago, just as the pandemic shut down our party, we began livestreaming on Twitch – and we’ve been going hard ever since!

But this weekend, we’re going especially hard, celebrating our 4-Year Twitchiversary! All six of our resident Twitch DJs are doing extended marathon sets, continuously streaming for over 60 hours from Friday through Sunday, March 8-10 (and maybe into Monday morning) with plenty of surprises along the way. We’ve even dropped a slew of new animated emotes, just in time for the occasion!

Check out the full schedule below, and we hope to see you in the ChatPod this weekend! Click on over to: twitch.tv/bootiemashup

All times are Pacific Time. Adjust accordingly and don’t forget about Daylight Savings Time on Saturday night!

For this second Cyberpunk: Bootie Mashup album, cover girl Adriana A invited Ohio-based producer (and fellow darksynth mashup producer) AGGRO1 to join her on this compilation, crafted specifically for Neotropolis 2024.

Eight brand-new mashups were created for this mixtape, including two collabs between Adriana A & AGGRO1, along with a dozen other tracks from these two producers that didn’t fit on last year’s edition. We tried to do a lot more ’80s & ’90s vocals this time!

This will be Bootie Mashup’s second year at Neotropolis, and Adriana A, along with Jupiter Gatling, will be closing out the 5-day cyberpunk festival on Saturday April 27 with a special DJ set at The Core.

Grafting popular vocals from the turn of the millennium with futuristic darksynth and mid-tempo bass, it’s the pop-infused soundtrack for a dystopian cyberpunk world.
